Architecture rules:

* Create a separate `incidenceknowledgeingestion` folder.
* Do not modify or destabilize `operationalknowledgeingestion`.
* Do not reuse old runtime/troubleshooting app code.
* Reuse existing extraction, artifact, context, runbook candidate, validation, and candidate pool logic only where clean and low-risk.
* Incident-specific logic must live in the new incidence folder.
* Incident runbook candidates must feed the same shared candidate pool used by operational/manual/training candidates.
* Incident workflow/playbook candidates should also be produced, but they are not approved canonical playbooks yet.
* Final runbooks must come from the finalized canonical runbook library after shared candidate pooling, cross-source merging, deduplication, synthesis, validation, and SME review.
* Incident-derived candidates may enrich canonical runbooks with observed failure modes, recovery details, validation checks, screenshots, logs, and escalation notes, but should not bypass the shared pool or create a separate final runbook library.
* Final workflows/playbooks must likewise be synthesized from workflow/playbook candidates after review. They should use finalized canonical runbooks as reusable action/procedure blocks rather than duplicating runbook steps.
* Draft workflow/playbook candidates must not contain detailed runbook instructions inside their nodes. Nodes should contain placeholders, short intent text, or "what this runbook/procedure should accomplish" descriptions so finalized runbooks can be pulled into playbooks later.
* Both canonical runbooks and canonical workflows/playbooks should produce human-reviewable Markdown files plus matching structured JSON records.
* Markdown files are for SME/product review and operational readability.
* JSON records are for validation, embeddings, Cosmos DB publishing, graph relationships, and runtime use in the troubleshooting app.
* Reviewed/approved runbooks, workflows/playbooks, operational context, source artifacts, and incident evidence records should be embedded and pushed to Cosmos DB/vector search only after validation gates pass.
* Preserve source lineage everywhere.
* Do not overwrite manual/operational outputs.
* Do not invent commands, service names, screenshots, access paths, SQL, API endpoints, or root causes.
* Separate observed signals from inferred causes.
* Validation status should default to `needs_sme_review`.
* Raw Salesforce, Teams, RCA, and screenshot data should not become final truth automatically.
* Everything incident-derived should be candidate/review-gated.

